  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency protection response for IDPs and critically at risk population affected by the Hawiga crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to respond to the unfolding emergency situation in Kirkuk and Salah al-Din Governorates and to contribute to first-line protection responses for urgent protection needs of Hawija crisis affected population. Through this project, INTERSOS will ensure that newly displaced and critically at-risk population are protected from further harm, and have access to timely and quality services, including legal assistance. Through a mobile approach, Hawija crisis affected people will be provided with timely and quality dissemination of key life-saving messages, information and awareness on protection risks, concepts and principles, and instructed on the services available in the area. Equally, these vulnerable population will be provided with legal assistance and information dissemination related to legal issues. Specifically, a strong and competent Legal team and protection monitoring team (trained on legal related matters) will be promptly established in order to immediately respond to the unfolding crisis and displacement towards Haj Ali camp mainly however, it will be as much flexible as possible in order to follow the flow of displacement, to respond to needs for legal assistance and protection monitoring in other locations in Ninewa. 
Finally INTERSOS has access, presence on the ground and capacities to respond to the urgent needs of the Hawija crisis affected population and will ensure a swift, efficient and coordinated protection response.</narrative>
  </description>
